 * The implementation attempts an atomic set-if-not-exists ({@code nx: true})
 * when the storage driver supports it, then verifies ownership by reading the
 * stored lock id. This prevents concurrent duplicate Creem webhooks from both
 * acquiring the lock and creating multiple Bifrost virtual keys.
